@startuml StudentEnrollmentStatus
title Student Enrollment Status (SMD-03)
hide empty description

' Color Customization
skinparam {
    BackgroundColor white
    ArrowColor #4C5FD5
    
    ' State Diagram specific
    StateBackgroundColor white
    StateBorderColor #4C5FD5
    StateStartColor #4C5FD5
    StateEndColor #4C5FD5
    
    ' Notes
    NoteBackgroundColor #FBBF24
    NoteBorderColor #FBBF24
}


state "Pending" as pending
note right of pending
The user has requested to join a private 
course and is waiting for 
Instructor/Admin approval. Content 
access is denied. 
end note

state "Active" as active
note right of active
The user is fully enrolled. They can 
view content, submit assignments, and 
receive grades. 
end note

state "Suspended" as suspended
note right of suspended
The enrollment is locked (e.g., 
non-payment or behavioral issue in this 
specific course). The user cannot access 
this course, though their account 
remains active elsewhere. 
end note

state "Expired" as expired
note right of expired
The enrollment duration (e.g., 6 months) 
has passed. Access is restricted or 
read-only. 
end note

state "Completed" as completed
note right of completed
The user has met all course completion 
criteria (grades/activities). They 
retain read-only access to their 
certificate. 
end note

null --> pending : Request Access()
null --> active : Self Enroll (Public Course)
pending --> active : Instructor Approves()
active --> suspended : Admin Suspends()
suspended --> active : Admin Unsuspends()
active --> expired : Time Limit Reached()
expired --> active : Extend/Renew()
active --> completed : Requirements Met()
any_state --> unenrolled : Drop Course()

@enduml
